Map.!doc: The Map object holds key-value pairs and remembers the original insertion order of the keys.

size.!doc: Returns the number of key/value pairs in the Map object.

clear.!doc: Removes all key/value pairs from the Map object.

delete.!doc: Removes the specified element from the Map object.

entries.!doc: Returns a new Iterator object that contains the [key, value] pairs.

forEach.!type: fn(callback: fn(value: ?, key: ?, map: +Map), thisArg?: ?) -> undefined
forEach.!doc: Calls callback once for each key-value pair.

get.!doc: Returns the value associated with the key, or undefined.

has.!doc: Returns a boolean asserting whether a value has been associated with the key.

keys.!doc: Returns a new Iterator object that contains the keys.

set.!doc: Sets the value for the key in the Map object.

values.!doc: Returns a new Iterator object that contains the values.

[@@iterator].!doc: Returns a new Iterator object with [key, value] pairs.
